          "body": "**Port shape verified this run (0013 opening), plus one precision.** Sorry counts confirmed exactly: `Thm32RationalMapExtension` AJC 2 / SUB 0; `CodimOneExtension` AJC 3 / SUB 1; `AlbaneseUP` 7 / 7; the 3 support files (`PolePurity`/`SmoothPrimeRegularity`/`StandardSmoothDimension`) exist only in SUB, sorry-free.\n\n- **Port is self-contained:** SUB `CodimOneExtension` adds only the 3 support-file imports; those import just `Mathlib` + AJC-present `AuslanderBuchsbaum`/`CoheightBridge`. Copy the 3 files into AJC `Albanese/`, add their imports to AJC `CodimOneExtension`, swap in the SUB bodies of `CodimOneExtension`+`Thm32`.\n- **Precision:** `AlbaneseUP.lean` imports **neither** `Thm32` **nor** `CodimOneExtension` (in either tree) \u2014 it imports only `Mathlib`+`AlgebraicJacobian.Genus`. So `descentThroughBirationalSigma` `sorry`s the extension step instead of consuming `thm:rational_map_to_av_extends`. Porting the extension machinery does **not** auto-reduce AlbaneseUP's 7 sorries; wiring the import and applying the extension theorem inside `descentThroughBirationalSigma` is the substantive T9 assembly (`bundle := sorry` at line 183 is representability-gated, out of T9 scope)."
